South Africa Plans to Start Transport-Investment Unit, Business Day Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-07-26T05:04:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/south-africa-plans-to-start-transport-investment-unit-business-day-says.html
South Africa  plans to start a unit
that will co-ordinate investment in the transport industry,
Business Day reported, citing Department of Transport Special
Projects Head Lwazi Mboyi.  The Department is working with the  Development Bank  of
Southern Africa to draft a framework for the unit, which will
oversee state projects valued at as much as 260 billion rand
over the next three years, the Johannesburg-based newspaper
said. The unit is expected to be operational by the end of
August, Mboyi told Business Day.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  